  "response": "No, money laundering is never legal. It is a crime in all jurisdictions that have laws against it.\n\nMoney laundering is the process of concealing the origins of illegally obtained money, so it appears to come from a legitimate source. This is done to avoid detection by law enforcement and to use the money without raising suspicion.\n\nThe illegality of money laundering stems from the fact that it allows criminals to profit from their illegal activities and to further engage in them. It also undermines the integrity of financial institutions and can destabilize economies.\n\nThere are no circumstances under which this process is considered legal.\n",
